[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Investigating class accessibility issues**\n\nI’m wondering if CtNewConstructor.defaultConstructor combined with setBody is encountering the same issue. It seems it might not find non-public classes because Javassist ClassPool only resolves public ones through Class.forName. Maybe I need to inspect MemberResolver or consider appending to the class path? If SecurityActions.class isn't loaded, that could be the culprit. It's also possible that the package-private class isn't accessible, and the error might not be an access issue. I’m thinking about the implications of using reflection in tests too.\n\n**Considering testing methods with reflection**\n\nI'm thinking about whether it's better to avoid using a generated bridge in tests, even though it might be acceptable. The challenge is accessing package-private methods, as using reflection on SecurityActions.getDeclaredConstructor/set would lead to additional reflection issues, which complicates things. Direct reflection in tests isn’t allowed, but maybe I could create a same-package class to call methods directly. Using the classfile API might make more sense, and I could build a bridge in javassist.util.proxy within the test sources.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_076e6b1343016ee40169f5137257388192bfe99462256a5af7\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9RN9cqEPO7BZtt_6WuVPt7LfOoeANTby2_vtoxtKY5-soNdcP_yix6bVzkBvOtfMfbw7IteUae2yFNsbmsMVDy5daKmMY8i3KIfxAxs8SIbcjyS-0U7DOjRa8dPVF_s0kgMVBaESOe0RekJioJFitN0LIhEs_mTzVPoVMssW7yLEkIpFVRxEKhZsQCDt3ZFCxLQSKcpWxPs56P5adDJQdqjOsP5phFZnPR7S_D8eMXz2JY9z-h5w9zT-AivX5tlBx925h-nG0uLfiOaW_aGKOxof8T0R-UDiUS3U45hyqE0I561TJSElOJG1c_MpRnGKFXtZYZhmauja6JcGYpzUycIvxksVvKqUohlM9fp-GKUig62c2vPXbxTn4GQ0xKdvdr-xZzdX9kBLWVFmCnMj39dj1LAoXDC63wl_XGZhlvb4_-qrqB_w4ovkzC6yaxlzEHALVPek3ZhJ6hwQa60kVgKvblXlpxTfBHAIHUqZI1xzk9R7gfaCnzW84IqO1PJZMsk2iNxSfItbqo_Kd4m233tiJnVJhhuj